maml:description.maml:para: Connects to the specified AppSense Management Server. All subsequent cmdlets will use this server for their operations.

The Connect-AppSenseManagementServerPackageServer cmdlet will create a connection to the specified AppSense Management Server using the provided credentials. If no credentials are provided then the user will prompted to enter some.
Specifies name of the AppSense Management Server to connect to. This can be either NetBIOS or FQDN. Only the hostname is required.
An object containing the credentials of a user to connect to the AppSense Management Server with.
The port number to use when connecting to the Management Server
When specified HTTPS will be used to connect to the Management Server
When provided the time will also be output to any verbosely written line.
Specifies name of the AppSense Management Server to connect to. This can be either NetBIOS or FQDN. Only the hostname is required.
The port number to use when connecting to the Management Server
When specified HTTPS will be used to connect to the Management Server

When provided the time will also be output to any verbosely written line.
The port number to use when connecting to the Management Server
When specified HTTPS will be used to connect to the Management Server
When provided the time will also be output to any verbosely written line.
When supplied the cmdlet will use the credentials of the executing user in order to connect to the AppSense Management Server.

$false if an error occurred or $true when a successful connection is made.

dev:remarks.maml:para: This example will use the credentials of the user executing the cmdlet to create a connection to the "APS-MGMT-01" server.
This example will prompt the user to enter the credentials required for connecting to "APS-MGMT-01".

The Get-AppSenseManagementServerPackage cmdlet retrieves details about the packages stored in the Management Server.
The name of the product to return packages for. This name must match that shown in the Packages section of the console.

maml:description.maml:para: Imports the specified package to the Management Server and optionally uploads the relevant pre-requisites.

The Import-AppSenseManagementServerPackage cmdlet imports the specified package to the Management Server and optionally uploads the relevant pre-requisites. Packages can be licenses, agents, configurations or patches to agents.
The full path to the package to import.
The path to the folder that contains any necessary pre-requites.
The description to assign to the package being imported.
The number of bytes to upload at a time.
If supplied, and the package is a configuration, the version number will be reset to Major.Minor.0.0
If supplied a standard progressbar is shown whilst uploading the given package.
When provided the time will also be output to any verbosely written line.
The full path to the package to import.
The path to the folder that contains any necessary pre-requites.
The description to assign to the package being imported.
The number of bytes to upload at a time.
If supplied, and the package is a configuration, the version number will be reset to Major.Minor.0.0
If supplied a standard progressbar is shown whilst uploading the given package.
When provided the time will also be output to any verbosely written line.
$true if the package was successfully imported and $false if an error occurred.

dev:remarks.maml:para: This example will import the 64-bit Environment Manager agent into the Management Server. The pre-requisites will also be uploaded from the path specified and associated with the agent. A progressbar will be shown whilst uploading packages and pre-requisites.
This example will upload the Environment Manger agent patch file from the specified location. A progressbar will be shown whilst uploading the file.
This example will import all licenses stored in the given msi file.
This example imports the configuration stored in the given MSI file.
This example imports the configuration stored in the given MSI file and resets the version number to Major.Minor.0.0
